					<head>Ecclesiastes scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80008490" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Ecclesiastes. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Kohelet</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">קהלת</title>
							<note>
								<p>The readings of the masoretic קרי are in almost all cases followed in the text, instead of כתיב. </p>
								<p>The 12th verse of chapter 12 is repeated at the end, though the siman יתק&quot;ק is not given. </p>
								<p>Verses 2-8 of chapter 3 are arranged in eight lines. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 15th to 16th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>4 membranes, 13 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>1900</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>4 membranes. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Darkening at head.</p>
									<p>Small patches of salt accretion. </p>
									<p>A few usage stains.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="13" ruledLines="28" writtenLines="28">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking. </p>
									<p>No tagin on שעטנזגץ. The letter ח is frequently arched. </p>
									<p>Breaks in the form of open sections at 7:1, 12:1, and at 2:1, 3:1, 4:1, 5:1, 6:1, 9:1, 10:1, 11:1 in the form of a closed section. </p>
									<p>No majuscular nor minuscular letters. Larger initial word of the scroll. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
